{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"I am known best for human-powered flight,"},{"time":7000,"text":"but that was just one thing that got me going"},{"time":12000,"text":"in the sort of things that I'm working in now."},{"time":16000,"text":"As a youngster, I was very interested in model airplanes,"},{"time":22000,"text":"ornithopters, autogyros, helicopters, gliders, power planes,"},{"time":28000,"text":"indoor models, outdoor models, everything,"},{"time":31000,"text":"which I just thought was a lot of fun,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and wondered why most other people didn't share my same enthusiasm with them."},{"time":42000,"text":"And then, navy pilot training, and, after college,"},{"time":48000,"text":"I got into sailplane flying, power plane flying,"},{"time":52000,"text":"and considered the sailplanes as a sort of hobby and fun,"},{"time":60000,"text":"but got tangled up with some great professor types,"},{"time":64000,"text":"who convinced me and everybody else in the field"},{"time":69000,"text":"that this was a good way to get into really deep science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"While this was all going on, I was in the field of weather modification,"},{"time":80000,"text":"although getting a Ph.D. in aeronautics."},{"time":84000,"text":"The weather modification subject was getting started,"},{"time":88000,"text":"and as a graduate student,"},{"time":90000,"text":"I could go around to the various talks that were being given,"},{"time":94000,"text":"on a hitchhiker ride to the East Coast,"},{"time":96000,"text":"and so on. And everybody would talk to me,"},{"time":99000,"text":"but all the professionals in the field hated each other,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and they wouldn't communicate. And as a result,"},{"time":105000,"text":"I got the absolutely unique background in that field,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and started a company, which did more research"},{"time":114000,"text":"in weather modification than anybody,"},{"time":118000,"text":"and there are a lot of things that I just can't go into."},{"time":124000,"text":"But then, 1971 started AeroVironment, with no employees --"},{"time":130000,"text":"then one or two, three,"},{"time":132000,"text":"and sort of fumbled along on trying to get interesting projects."},{"time":136000,"text":"We had AirDynamisis,"},{"time":138000,"text":"who, like I, did not want to work for aerospace companies"},{"time":143000,"text":"on some big, many year project,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and so we did our small projects, and the company slowly grew."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"The thing that is exciting was, in 1976,"},{"time":161000,"text":"I suddenly got interested in the human-powered airplane"},{"time":166000,"text":"because I'd made a made a loan to a friend of 100,000 dollars,"},{"time":170000,"text":"or I guaranteed the money at the bank."},{"time":172000,"text":"He needed them -- he needed the money for starting a company."},{"time":176000,"text":"The company did not succeed, and he couldn't pay the money back,"},{"time":179000,"text":"and I was the guarantor of the note. So, I had a $100,000 debt,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and I noticed that the Kramer prize for human-powered flight,"},{"time":190000,"text":"which had then been around for -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":194000,"text":"17 years at the time, was 50,000 pounds,"},{"time":197000,"text":"which, at the exchange rate, was just about 100,000 dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"So suddenly, I was interested in human-powered flight --"},{"time":204000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":207000,"text":"and did not -- the way I approached it, first,"},{"time":213000,"text":"thinking about ways to make the planes,"},{"time":216000,"text":"was just like they'd been doing in England, and not succeeding,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and I gave it up. I figured, nah, there isn't any simple, easy way."},{"time":225000,"text":"But then, got off on a vacation trip, and was studying bird flight,"},{"time":231000,"text":"just for the fun of it,"},{"time":233000,"text":"and you can watch a bird soaring around in circles,"},{"time":236000,"text":"and measure the time, and estimate the bank angle,"},{"time":240000,"text":"and immediately, figure out its speed,"},{"time":243000,"text":"and the turning radius, and so on,"},{"time":246000,"text":"which I could do in the car, as we're driving along on a vacation trip --"},{"time":251000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":253000,"text":"with my three sons, young sons, helping me,"},{"time":257000,"text":"but ridiculing the whole thing very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261000,"text":"But that began thinking about how birds went around,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and then how airplanes would, how hang gliders would fly,"},{"time":273000,"text":"and then other planes,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and the idea of the Gossamer-Condor-type airplane quickly emerged,"},{"time":281000,"text":"was so logical, one should have thought of it in the first place,"},{"time":284000,"text":"but one didn't. And it was just, keep the weight down --"},{"time":288000,"text":"70 pounds was all it weighed -- but let the size swell up, like a hang glider,"},{"time":295000,"text":"but three times the span, three times the cord."},{"time":297000,"text":"You're down to a third of the speed, a third of the power,"},{"time":300000,"text":"and a good bicyclist can put out that power, and that worked,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and we won the prize a year later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312000,"text":"We didn't -- a lot of flying, a lot of experiments, a lot of things that didn't work,"},{"time":318000,"text":"and ones that did work, and the plane kept getting a little better, a little better."},{"time":323000,"text":"Got a good pilot, Brian Allen, to operate it,"},{"time":326000,"text":"and finally, succeeded. But unfortunately,"},{"time":330000,"text":"about 65,000 dollars was spent on the project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"And there was only about 30 to help retire the debt."},{"time":340000,"text":"But fortunately, Henry Kramer, who put up the prize for --"},{"time":344000,"text":"that was a one-mile flight -- put up a new prize"},{"time":346000,"text":"for flying the English Channel, 21 miles."},{"time":349000,"text":"And he thought it would take another 18 years for somebody to win that."},{"time":353000,"text":"We realized that if you just cleaned up our Gossamer Condor a little bit,"},{"time":359000,"text":"the power to fly would be decreased a little bit,"},{"time":363000,"text":"and if you decrease the power required a little,"},{"time":366000,"text":"the pilot can fly a much longer period of time."},{"time":369000,"text":"And Brian Allen was able, in a miraculous flight,"},{"time":373000,"text":"to get the Gossamer Albatross across the English Channel,"},{"time":377000,"text":"and we won the 100,000-pound, 200,000-dollar prize for that."},{"time":384000,"text":"And when all expenses were paid, the debt was handled, and everything was fine."},{"time":392000,"text":"It turned out that giving the planes to the museum"},{"time":395000,"text":"was worth much more than the debt,"},{"time":399000,"text":"so for five years, six years, I only had to pay one third income tax."},{"time":406000,"text":"So, there were good economic reasons for the project, but --"},{"time":411000,"text":"(Laughter) --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"that's not, well, the project was done entirely for economic reasons,"},{"time":421000,"text":"and we have not been involved in any human-powered flight since then --"},{"time":425000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":427000,"text":"because the prizes are all over."},{"time":431000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":432000,"text":"But that sure started me thinking about various things,"},{"time":436000,"text":"and immediately, we began making a solar-powered plane"},{"time":441000,"text":"because we felt solar power was going to be so important"},{"time":444000,"text":"for the country and the world,"},{"time":446000,"text":"we didn't want the small funding in the government to be decreased,"},{"time":451000,"text":"which is what the government was trying to do with it."},{"time":453000,"text":"And we thought a solar-powered plane wouldn't really make sense,"},{"time":458000,"text":"but you could do it and it would get a lot of publicity for solar power"},{"time":462000,"text":"and maybe help that field."},{"time":464000,"text":"And that project continued, did succeed,"},{"time":468000,"text":"and we then got into other projects in aviation"},{"time":474000,"text":"and mechanical things and ground devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482000,"text":"But while this was going on,"},{"time":485000,"text":"in 1982, I got a prize from the Lindbergh Foundation --"},{"time":490000,"text":"their annual prize --"},{"time":492000,"text":"and I had to prepare a paper on it,"},{"time":496000,"text":"which collected all my varied thoughts"},{"time":499000,"text":"and varied interests over the years."},{"time":501000,"text":"This was the one chance that I had to focus on what I, really, was after,"},{"time":506000,"text":"and what was important. And to my surprise,"},{"time":510000,"text":"I realized the importance of environmental issues,"},{"time":515000,"text":"which Charles Lindbergh devoted the last third of his life to,"},{"time":520000,"text":"and preparing that paper did me a lot of good."},{"time":526000,"text":"I thought back about if I was a space traveler,"},{"time":529000,"text":"and came and visited Earth every 5,000 years."},{"time":532000,"text":"And for a few thousand visits, I would see the same thing every time,"},{"time":539000,"text":"the little differences in the Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"But this last time, just coming round, right now,"},{"time":545000,"text":"suddenly, there'd be huge changes in the environment,"},{"time":550000,"text":"in the concentration of people,"},{"time":553000,"text":"and it was just unbelievable, the amount of -- all the change in it."},{"time":565000,"text":"I wanted to -- well, one of the biggest changes is, 200 years ago,"},{"time":570000,"text":"we began using coal from underground, which has a lot of pollution,"},{"time":576000,"text":"and 100 years ago, began getting gasoline from underground,"},{"time":580000,"text":"with a lot of pollution. And gasoline consumption, or production,"},{"time":586000,"text":"will reach its limit in about ten years, and then go down,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and we wonder what's going to happen with transportation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597000,"text":"I wanted to show the slide --"},{"time":600000,"text":"this slide, I think, is the most important one any of you will see, ever, because --"},{"time":609000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":611000,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":614000,"text":"it shows nature versus humans, and goes from 1850 to 2050."},{"time":621000,"text":"And so, the year 2000, you see there."},{"time":624000,"text":"And this is the weight of all air and land vertebrates."},{"time":629000,"text":"Humans and muskrats and giraffes and birds and so on, are --"},{"time":634000,"text":"the red line goes up. That's the humans and livestock and pets portion."},{"time":641000,"text":"The green line goes down. That's the wild nature portion."},{"time":645000,"text":"Humans, livestock and pets are, now, 98 percent of the total world's mass"},{"time":651000,"text":"of vertebrates on land and air."},{"time":654000,"text":"And you don't know what the future will hold,"},{"time":657000,"text":"but it's not going to get a lower percentage."},{"time":661000,"text":"Ten thousand years ago, the humans and livestock and pets"},{"time":665000,"text":"were not even one tenth of one percent"},{"time":667000,"text":"and wouldn't even have been visible on such a curve."},{"time":671000,"text":"Now they are 98 percent, and it, I think, shows human domination of the Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682000,"text":"I give a talk to some remarkable high school students each summer,"},{"time":689000,"text":"and ask them, after they've asked me questions,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and I give them a talk and so on. Then I ask them questions."},{"time":696000,"text":"What's the population of the Earth?"},{"time":698000,"text":"What's the population of the Earth going to be"},{"time":700000,"text":"when you're the age of your parents?"},{"time":702000,"text":"Which I'd never, really -- they had never, really, thought about"},{"time":704000,"text":"but, now, they think about it."},{"time":706000,"text":"And then, what population of the Earth would be an equilibrium"},{"time":713000,"text":"that could continue on, and be for 2050, 2100, 2150?"},{"time":719000,"text":"And they form little groups, all fighting with each other,"},{"time":722000,"text":"and when I leave, two hours later,"},{"time":724000,"text":"most of them are saying about 2 billion people,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and they don't have any clue about how to get down to 2 billion,"},{"time":733000,"text":"nor do I, but I think they're right and this is a serious problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741000,"text":"Rachel Carson was thinking of these, and came out with \"Silent Spring,\" way back."},{"time":748000,"text":"\"Solar Manifesto\" by Hermann Scheer, in Germany,"},{"time":752000,"text":"claims all energy on Earth can be derived, for every country,"},{"time":757000,"text":"from solar energy and water, and so on."},{"time":765000,"text":"You don't need to dig down for these chemicals,"},{"time":768000,"text":"and we can do things much more efficiently."},{"time":772000,"text":"Let's have the next slide."},{"time":774000,"text":"So this just summarizes it. \"Over billions of years,"},{"time":777000,"text":"on a unique sphere, chance has painted a thin covering of life --"},{"time":780000,"text":"complex and probable, wonderful and fragile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"Suddenly, we humans, a recently arrived species,"},{"time":786000,"text":"no longer subject to the checks and balances inherent in nature,"},{"time":790000,"text":"have grown in population, technology and intelligence"},{"time":793000,"text":"to a position of terrible power. We, now, wield the paintbrush.\""},{"time":797000,"text":"We're in charge. It's frightening."},{"time":801000,"text":"And I do a painting every 20 or 25 years. This is the last one."},{"time":806000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":808000,"text":"And [it] shows the Earth in a time flag: on the right,"},{"time":812000,"text":"in trilobites and dinosaurs and so on;"},{"time":815000,"text":"and over the triangle, we now get to civilization and TV"},{"time":820000,"text":"and traffic jams and so on."},{"time":822000,"text":"I have no idea of what comes next,"},{"time":825000,"text":"so I just used robotic and natural cockroaches as the future,"},{"time":830000,"text":"as a little warning."},{"time":832000,"text":"And two weeks after this drawing was done,"},{"time":835000,"text":"we actually had our first project contract, at AeroVironment,"},{"time":839000,"text":"on robotic cockroaches, which was very frightening to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":846000,"text":"(Paper rustling)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":849000,"text":"Well, that'll be all the slides."},{"time":856000,"text":"As time went on, we stopped our environmental programs."},{"time":859000,"text":"We focused more on the really serious energy problems"},{"time":864000,"text":"of the future, and we produced products for the company."},{"time":871000,"text":"And we developed the impact car that General Motors made,"},{"time":876000,"text":"the EV1, out of --"},{"time":879000,"text":"and got the Air Resources Board to have the regulations"},{"time":886000,"text":"that stimulated the electric cars, but they've since come apart."},{"time":890000,"text":"And we've done a lot of things, small drone airplanes and so on."},{"time":897000,"text":"I have a Helios. We have the first video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"(Video) Narrator: With a wingspan of 247 feet, this makes her larger than a Boeing 747."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918000,"text":"Her designers' attention to detail and her construction"},{"time":921000,"text":"gives Helios' structure the flexibility and strength"},{"time":924000,"text":"to deal with the turbulence encountered in the atmosphere."},{"time":927000,"text":"This enables her to easily ride through the air currents"},{"time":930000,"text":"as if she's sliding along on the ocean waves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"Paul MacCready: The wings could touch together on top and not break. We think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":938000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":941000,"text":"Narrator: And Helios now begins the process of turning her back to the sun,"},{"time":944000,"text":"to maximize the power from her solar array."}]},{"cues":[{"time":947000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":955000,"text":"As the sky gets darker, and the outside air temperatures drop"},{"time":959000,"text":"below minus 100 degrees Fahrenheit,"},{"time":962000,"text":"the most environmentally hostile segment of Helios's journey"},{"time":965000,"text":"has gone by without notice,"},{"time":967000,"text":"except for being recorded by specially designed data acquisition systems"},{"time":971000,"text":"and their associated sensors."},{"time":974000,"text":"Approaching a peak radar altitude of 96,863 feet,"},{"time":979000,"text":"at 4:12 p.m., Helios is standing on top of 98 percent of the Earth's atmosphere."},{"time":984000,"text":"This is more than 10,000 feet higher"},{"time":987000,"text":"than the previous world's altitude record held by the SR-71 Blackbird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001000,"text":"PM: That plane has many purposes, but it's aimed for communications,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and it can fly so slowly that it'll just stay up at 65,000 feet."},{"time":1013000,"text":"Eventually, it will be able to have to stay up day, night, day, night,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"for six months at a time, acting like the synchronous satellite,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"but only ten miles above the Earth."},{"time":1022000,"text":"Let's have the next video. This shows the other end of the spectrum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025000,"text":"(Video) Narrator: A tiny airplane, the AV Pointer serves for surveillance."},{"time":1028000,"text":"In effect a pair of roving eyeglasses,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"a cutting-edge example of where miniaturization can lead"},{"time":1033000,"text":"if the operator is remote from the vehicle."},{"time":1036000,"text":"It is convenient to carry, assemble, and launch by hand."},{"time":1039000,"text":"Battery-powered, it is silent and rarely noticed."},{"time":1043000,"text":"It sends high-resolution video pictures back to the operator."},{"time":1046000,"text":"With on-board GPS, it can navigate autonomously,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"and it is rugged enough to self-land without damage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"PM: Okay, and let's have the next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1056000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060000,"text":"That plane is widely used by the military, now, in all their operations."},{"time":1065000,"text":"Let's have the next video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1069000,"text":"(Video) (Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083000,"text":"Alan Alda: He's got it, he's got it, he's got it on his head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087000,"text":"We're going to end our visit with Paul MacCready's flying circus"},{"time":1090000,"text":"by meeting his son, Tyler, who, with his two brothers,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"helped build the Gossamer Condor, 25 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1097000,"text":"Tyler MacCready: You can chase it, like this, for hours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1099000,"text":"AA: When they got bored with their father's project,"},{"time":1102000,"text":"they invented an extraordinary little plane of their own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1104000,"text":"TM: And I can control it by putting the lift on one side of the wing, or on the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109000,"text":"AA: They called it their Walkalong Glider."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1111000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1113000,"text":"I've never seen anything like that."},{"time":1114000,"text":"How old were you when you invented that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116000,"text":"TM: Oh, 10, 11. (AA: Oh my God.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1119000,"text":"TM: 12, something like that. (AA: That's amazing.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121000,"text":"PM: And Tyler's here to show you the Walkalong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1129000,"text":"TM: All right. You all got a couple of these in your gift bags,"},{"time":1133000,"text":"and one of the first things,"},{"time":1136000,"text":"the production version seemed to dive a little bit,"},{"time":1138000,"text":"and so I would just suggest you bend the wing tips up a little bit"},{"time":1141000,"text":"before you try flying it."},{"time":1143000,"text":"I'll give you a demonstration of how it works."},{"time":1145000,"text":"The idea is that it soars on the lift over your body, like a seagull soaring on a cliff."},{"time":1151000,"text":"As the wind comes up, it has to go over the cliff, so"},{"time":1154000,"text":"as you walk through the air, it goes around your body, some has to go over you."},{"time":1159000,"text":"And so you just keep the glider positioned in that up current."},{"time":1162000,"text":"The launch is the difficult part: you've got to hold it high up, over your head,"},{"time":1165000,"text":"and you start walking forward, and just let go of it, and you can control it like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1171000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1173000,"text":"And then also, like it said in the video,"},{"time":1176000,"text":"you can turn it left or right"},{"time":1178000,"text":"just by putting the lift under one wing or another."},{"time":1180000,"text":"So I can do it -- oops, that was going to be a right turn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1185000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1186000,"text":"Okay, this one will be a left turn."},{"time":1190000,"text":"Here, but --"},{"time":1192000,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":1193000,"text":"anyway."},{"time":1195000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1198000,"text":"And that's it, so you can just control it, wherever you want,"},{"time":1201000,"text":"and it's just hours of fun. And these are no longer in production,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"so you have real collector's items."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1207000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1209000,"text":"And this, we just wanted to show you --"},{"time":1214000,"text":"if we can get the video running on this, yeah --"},{"time":1216000,"text":"just an example of a little video surveillance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1222000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1224000,"text":"This was flying around in the party last night, and --"},{"time":1228000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":1230000,"text":"you can see how it just can fly around,"},{"time":1233000,"text":"and you can spy on anybody you want."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1235000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1241000,"text":"And that's it. I was going to bring an airplane,"},{"time":1243000,"text":"but I was worried about hitting people in here,"},{"time":1245000,"text":"so I thought this would be a little bit more gentle."},{"time":1249000,"text":"And that's it, yeah, just a few inventions."},{"time":1252000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1260000,"text":"All right."}]}]}